Petilium Cerialem] Cerialis had once been lieutenant of the 9th legion in Britain, under Suetonius Paulinus. He was connected by marriage with Vespasian and was one of his generals in the civil war. He was engaged in the capture of Rome, and was afterwards despatched into Germany to oppose Civilis and the Batavi. He appears to have died during his command in Britain.
